ZH: 请把这些东西放到别处，不要碍事。
EN: Please put these things elsewhere, don't get in the way.

ZH: 这张桌子太大了，很碍事。
EN: This table is too big, it is very obstructive.

ZH: 这根电线挂在门旁边，真的很碍事。
EN: This wire hanging beside the door is really in the way.

ZH: 别站在门口，你会碍事。
EN: Don't stand at the doorway, you will obstruct.

ZH: 这个摄像机放在这里会碍事。
EN: This camera will block the way if placed here.

ZH: 不要将行李箱放在过道里，它会碍事。
EN: Don't put the suitcase in the aisle, it will get in the way.

ZH: 他一直呆在电视前，碍事了。
EN: He stayed in front of the TV all the time, getting in the way.

ZH: 在医院停车场里停车是被认为是很碍事的。
EN: Parking in the hospital parking lot is considered obstructive.

ZH: 这个建筑工地占据了整条街，真的很碍事。
EN: This construction site is taking over the whole street, it is very obstructive.

ZH: 他在公共交通工具上大声讲电话，很碍事。
EN: He spoke loudly on the public transportation, causing inconvenience.

ZH: 当有人在街上乱扔垃圾，会碍事。
EN: It is obstructive when someone randomly throws garbage on the street.

ZH: 当你跳队列的时候，会碍到其他人。
EN: Cutting the line will inconvenience others.

ZH: 在超市的通道里停下来聊天，真的很碍事。
EN: Stopping in the aisle to chat at the supermarket is really obstructive.

ZH: 请收拾一下你的床铺，让别人能够通过，不要碍事。
EN: Please tidy up your bed, so others can pass through, don't be in the way.

ZH: 他的车停在了马路中间，阻碍了交通，真的很碍事。
EN: His car is parked in the middle of the road, blocking traffic, it is really obstructive.

ZH: 在工作会议上用手机打电话是很碍事的。
EN: Using the phone to make calls during a work meeting is very obstructive.

ZH: 当地铁人满为患时，不要在门口挤行。
EN: Don't push your way around the door when the subway is overcrowded.

ZH: 不要站在楼梯口看手机，会碍到别人。
EN: Don't stand in the stairway and look at your phone, it will inconvenience others.

ZH: 在电梯里留下空间给其他人进来，不要碍事。
EN: Leave space in the elevator for others to enter, don't get in the way.

ZH: 当有人需要通过时，请让行人道畅通。
EN: Please keep the pedestrian passage clear when someone needs to pass through.
